node.title: Swedish House Mafia, The Weeknd replace Ye as Coachella headliners
node.description: Ye's withdrawal as a headliner follows heavy criticism over his online actions.

node.title: Diego Maradona's "Hand of God" jersey may sell for $5.2 million
node.description: The Argentine legend's goal was ruled a header, but the ball had bounced off Maradona's fist, out of sight of the referee.

node.title: House to vote on criminal referrals for Trump aides Navarro and Scavino
node.description: The motion would refer contempt charges against former Trump aides Peter Navarro and Dan Scavino for not complying with subpoenas by the House January 6 committee.

node.title: What Elon Musk's seat on Twitter's board could mean for users
node.description: As its biggest shareholder, the billionaire business magnate could reshape the social media platform. Here's how.

node.title: No charges will be filed in no-knock warrant killing of Amir Locke
node.description: Authorities said there was "insufficient admissible evidence" to file charges in the case.

node.title: New national research effort focuses on mysteries of long COVID
node.description: The White House also acknowledged that long COVID appears to be a disability, meaning that patients could be entitled to federal legal protections.

node.title: New sanctions by U.S. and allies target Putin's daughters and Russian banks
node.description: The sanctions were announced in coordination with the Group of 7 and European Union.

node.title: China warns against "unfounded accusations" over Ukraine atrocities
node.description: The Chinese foreign minister said Russia can't be blamed for the "deeply disturbing" civilian deaths near Kyiv until the "full picture is clear."

node.title: Trial of accused Sarah Lawrence College sex-trafficker goes to jury
node.description: Lawrence Ray turned to physical abuse and psychological torment to extort money, sex and other favors, prosecutors say.

node.title: Ed Sheeran wins "Shape of You" copyright lawsuit
node.description: This is not the first time the song has been compared to another. In 2017, Sheeran gave credit to Kandi Burruss and others who wrote "No Scrubs," because his song sounded similar.

node.title: China stops separating families under COVID lockdown amid outcry
node.description: The change to the draconian "zero-COVID" policies came as China's largest city struggled to contain the virus, reporting another record number of new cases.

node.title: Senate Republicans block effort to advance $10 billion COVID relief deal
node.description: The White House called the Senate vote a "step backward" for the Biden administration's ability to respond to COVID-19.

node.title: Ukraine already investigating almost 4,500 alleged Russian war crimes
node.description: "They just killed him": Bucha resident recounts Russian troops' murder of her husband as Ukrainian investigators document atrocities.

node.title: U.S. to send $100 million in Javelin missiles to Ukraine
node.description: The latest transfer brings the total amount of military aid from the U.S. to Ukraine to more than $2.4 billion since Mr. Biden assumed office.

node.title: Former Trump appointee advances to runoff for Rep. Devin Nunes' seat
node.description: The second runoff spot hasn't been determined yet, and finishing the count will take at least a week, since mail ballots can arrive as late as April 12.

node.title: Doctor found dead near waterfall days after she was reported missing
node.description: Kelsey Musgrove had been hiking at Potato River Falls​ in Iron County and last had contact with people on March 26.

node.title: College student found dead near school, ex-football player arrested
node.description: Keenan Harpole was booked on suspicion of second-degree murder, domestic violence and unlawful use of a weapon.

node.title: U.S. developing hypersonic missiles with U.K. and Australia
node.description: The move comes as China and Russia make rapid advances in their programs. Hypersonic missiles are so fast they can't be intercepted by any current missile defense system.

node.title: Pope Francis kisses a Ukrainian flag, denounces "massacre in Bucha"
node.description: The pope lamented "cruelty that is increasingly horrendous" in Russia's war on Ukraine and slammed the "impotence of international organizations" for failing to stop it.

node.title: Toddler shoots 4-year-old sister to death inside car at gas station
node.description: Last year, there were at least 379 unintentional shootings by children nationwide, resulting in 154 deaths, one group estimates.

node.title: Energy expert Mark Finely on global effects of Russia's war in Ukraine
node.description: Finley explains the effects of Russia's invasion of Ukraine on global oil and gas markets and discusses the risk of a recession.

node.title: GOP Senate push focuses on Latinos with "Vamos" initiative, Title 42
node.description: The NRSC's new multi-million-dollar "Vamos" initiative, first shared with CBS News, will target 2022 races in nine battleground states.

node.title: U.S. OK's up to $95 million to support Taiwan's Patriot missile system
node.description: The latest arms purchase comes as Taiwan closely watches the ongoing Russia-Ukraine war, as it also lives under the constant threat of an invasion by a giant neighbor.

node.title: Netherlands seizes 14 yachts as Russia faces new sanctions over Ukraine
node.description: The Dutch government said the "vessels cannot be delivered, transferred or exported" while their ownership is investigated for links to the Kremlin.

node.title: Airbnb lashes out at Christchurch housing rule changes
node.description: Airbnb has called new home sharing regulations in Christchurch restrictive and outdated.

node.title: Not all heroes wear capes - some drive bulldozers
node.description: As heavy rain fell in northern Hawke's Bay two weeks ago, Hamish Pryde waded his bulldozer through deep water to reach the Wairoa River, where he worked till nightfall to stop a potential disaster.

node.title: Road User Charges bill passes, taking effect 21 April
node.description: A bill discounting road user charges by 36 percent has passed its third reading in Parliament.

node.title: Oklahoma passes near-total abortion ban with threat of jail for providers
node.description: Lawmakers have passed a bill that would make it illegal to perform an abortion in the state except in medical emergencies.

node.title: Franchisees allege 7-Eleven model based on wage theft
node.description: Convenience store giant 7-Eleven is set to pay out almost $A100m after being hit with class actions by Australian franchisees.

node.title: U.S. helps China seek clues on plane's deadly nosedive into a mountain
node.description: Both black boxes from the China Eastern Airlines 737 that crashed last month, killing all 132 on board, are with NTSB experts in Washington.
